-- Robredo Beats Anderson in Casablanca Tennis Final; Vinci Wins
-- B y   P e t e r - J o s e p h   H e g a r t y
-- 2013-04-14T18:46:14Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-04-14/robredo-beats-anderson-in-casablanca-tennis-final-vinci-wins.html
Spain’s Tommy Robredo upset  Kevin
Anderson  of South Africa in three sets to win the final of the
ATP Grand Prix Hassan II tennis tournament in Casablanca,
Morocco.  Robredo won 7-6 (8-6), 4-6, 6-3 for his 11th ATP Tour title
and the first since 2011.  Italy’s Roberta Vinci defeated Petra Kvitova of the Czech
Republic 7-6 (7-2), 6-1 to win the final of the WTA BNP Paribas
Katowice Open in Poland.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Peter-Joseph Hegarty at 
 phegarty@bloomberg.net  